<h2>
	Welcome to Laterz!
</h2>

<em>Laterz is an app that let's you save URLs for viewing at a later time.</em>

<ul>

<li>Maybe you find a web site that you want to check out later.</li>

<li>Maybe you are at work and stumble on a <a href="http://www.iamlost.com/features/robotporn/" title="YPL: Vintage Robot Porn">robot porn</a> site and don't want to get caught browsing.</li>

<li>Or maybe you are like me and like to compile URLs for a blog posts, and end up with scads of these one-off bookmark folders that end up getting deleted when you are done.</li>

</ul>

<p>If you you fit any of these, Laterz can be your huckleberry.</p>

<p>A <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time_shifting" title="Time shifting - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia">time shifting</a> service for URLs, Laterz lets you save and categorize URLs with the click of a button.</p>

<p>Submit using a normal form or use a bookmark bar shortcut to make saving quicker and easier.</p>

<p>See <span  style="font-size: 2.0em"><%= link_to "how it works", how_it_works_path %></span></p>

